<div class="contextHeader">

<span class="contextHeadline">
<!-- field-start:cite -->38 USC 3111<!-- field-end:cite -->: Regulations to promote satisfactory conduct and cooperation</span>
<span class="lawsInEffect">Text contains those laws in effect on May 24, 2026</span>
<!-- pending-update-statement -->
<!-- field-start:expcite -->

<div class="expCite">
<span class="titleExpcite">From Title 38-VETERANS' BENEFITS</span><span class="parent1ExpCite">PART III-READJUSTMENT AND RELATED BENEFITS</span><span class="parent2ExpCite">CHAPTER 31-TRAINING AND REHABILITATION FOR VETERANS WITH SERVICE-CONNECTED DISABILITIES</span>
</div>
<!-- field-end:expcite -->

<div class="jumpTo">
<span class="jumpToHeader">Jump To: </span><span class="jumpToField"><a href="#sourcecredit">Source Credit</a></span><span class="jumpToField"><a href="#miscellaneous-note">Miscellaneous</a></span><span class="jumpToField"><a href="#priorprovisions-note">Prior Provisions</a></span><span class="jumpToField"><a href="#amendment-note">Amendments</a></span><span class="jumpToField"><a href="#effectivedate-note">Effective Date</a></span>
</div>

</div>
<!-- documentid:38_3111  usckey:380000000311100000000000000000000 currentthrough:20260430_119-87 documentPDFPage:-1 -->
<!-- itempath:/380/PART III/CHAPTER 31/Sec. 3111 -->
<!-- itemsortkey:380AAWQ -->
<!-- expcite:TITLE 38-VETERANS&apos; BENEFITS!@!PART III-READJUSTMENT AND RELATED BENEFITS!@!<usCode chapter="31" edition="prelim" title="38">CHAPTER 31</usCode>-TRAINING AND REHABILITATION FOR VETERANS WITH SERVICE-CONNECTED DISABILITIES!@!Sec. 3111 -->
<!-- field-start:head -->

<h3 class="section-head">&sect;3111. Regulations to promote satisfactory conduct and cooperation</h3>
<!-- field-end:head -->
<!-- field-start:statute -->

<p class="statutory-body">The Secretary shall prescribe such rules and regulations as the Secretary determines necessary to promote satisfactory conduct and cooperation on the part of veterans who are pursuing rehabilitation programs under this chapter. In any case in which the Secretary determines that a veteran has failed to maintain satisfactory conduct or cooperation, the Secretary may, after determining that all reasonable counseling efforts have been made and are not reasonably likely to be effective, discontinue services and assistance unless the Secretary determines that mitigating circumstances exist. In any case in which such services and assistance have been discontinued, the Secretary may reinstitute such services and assistance only if the Secretary determines that-</p>

<a name="substructure-location_1"></a>

<p class="statutory-body-1em">(1) the cause of the unsatisfactory conduct or cooperation of such veteran has been removed; and</p>

<a name="substructure-location_2"></a>

<p class="statutory-body-1em">(2) the rehabilitation program which such veteran proposes to pursue (whether the same or revised) is suitable to such veteran's abilities, aptitudes, and interests.</p>
<!-- field-end:statute -->

<a name="sourcecredit"></a>
<!-- field-start:sourcecredit -->

<p class="source-credit">(Added <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=94&page=2181" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> title I, &sect;101(a), Oct. 17, 1980, <statuteAtLarge page="2181" volume="94">94 Stat. 2181</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, &sect;1511; amended <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=103&page=2092" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> title IV, &sect;423(b)(1)(A), Dec. 18, 1989, <statuteAtLarge page="2092" volume="103">103 Stat. 2092</statuteAtLarge>
</a>; renumbered &sect;3111, <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=105&page=406" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(a), Aug. 6, 1991, <statuteAtLarge page="406" volume="105">105 Stat. 406</statuteAtLarge>
</a>.)</p>

<br class="Q04">
<!-- field-end:sourcecredit -->
<!-- field-start:notes -->

<a name="miscellaneous-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Editorial Notes</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="priorprovisions-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:priorprovisions-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Prior Provisions</h4>

<p class="note-body">Prior section 3111 was renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('5311', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 5311 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:priorprovisions-note -->

<a name="amendment-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:amendment-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Amendments</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1991</b>-<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83</pLaw> renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('1511', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 1511 of this title</span> as this section.</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1989</b>-<pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237</pLaw> substituted "Secretary" for "Administrator" wherever appearing.</p>

<br class="Q04">
<!-- field-end:amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="effectivedate-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date</h4>

<p class="note-body">Section effective Apr. 1, 1981, see section 802(a)(1) of <pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> set out as a note under <span onclick="openDocument('3100', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 3100 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->





